# Compiled binaries. `go build -o ear ./cmd/ear` in the repo root is the
# documented way to try the CLI, so the result must never be committable.
/ear
*.exe
*.test
*.out

# Go tooling
vendor/
coverage.txt
coverage.html

# Runtime state EAR itself writes: the persisted audit trail, the
# cross-session store, and anything else a stack declares under `.ear/`.
# Running a stack must never dirty the fixture it ran against.
.ear/

# Credentials. memory.md only ever names the env var holding a key, never
# the key -- keep it that way on disk too.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.key
key.txt

.DS_Store
